Company Name: As a steadfast advocate for manufacturing activities, the Federation of Malaysian Manufacturers (FMM) has supplied crucial insights to the Government and played a pivotal role in the development of our nation's industrial landscape. Its dedication to champion industry players aligns with the Government's vision for a robust and competitive manufacturing sector.
Address: The manufacturing sector is a key economic driver for the country, generating strong economic multipliers that catapulted Malaysia's development. With this in mind, the Ekonomi MADANI framework has underscored the importance of reigniting :he manufacturing sector as Malaysia's growth engine. Going forward, Malaysia is on track to be a preferred regional supply chain and manufacturing hub in the ASEAN region., Several strategic initiatives are underway. The Government has earmarked RM 100 million for the enhancement of industrial areas, with a specific focus on the implementation of sustainable and green concepts. This funding will be directed towards the completion of infrastructure projects, ensuring that our industrial zones align with environmentally conscious practices., Another RM 100 million will be directed towards amplifying the research, development, commercialisation, and innovation (R&D&C&I) ecosystem, targeting key areas such as industrial needs, renewable energy, food security, and emerging growth sectors. This will bolster the manufacturing sector's resilience and competitiveness on both domestic and global fronts, to ensure that the country's manufacturing sector speeds ahead to the forefront of intellectual properties., The Ekonomi MADANI framework sets bold benchmarks for the next decade, with a vision to position Malaysia as the region's most dynamic economy. Key to bringing this vision to life is the New Industrial Master Plan 2030 (NIMP), that aims to pivot Malaysia’s manufacturing sector to one with more added value, thereby enhancing Malaysia's competitive edge in the region.

Company Name: Congratulations to the Federation of Malaysian Manufacturers (FMM) on the publication of the 54th Edition of FMM Directory of Malaysian Industries, which also testifies to the federation's meaningful contribution and service to its members for over five decades. As we celebrate FMM's anniversary, it is also an opportune moment to acknowledge its role in contributing to Malaysia's prosperity, and how FMM's strong partnership could help drive the manufacturing sector's growth in the coming years.
Address: Looking ahead, the Ministry of Investment, Trade & Industry’s (MITI) responsibility on achieving the Government's MADANI vision is clear: to strengthen Malaysia's economy by building a resilient, diversified, and sustainable manufacturing sector, which would, in turn, grow exports. To that end, MITI is committed to fostering an environment that not only supports the immediate needs of the manufacturing sector, but also reinvigorates it for enduring success., At the core of MITI's commitment is the New Industrial Master Plan 2030 (NIMP2030) - a transformative policy launched in 2023 - designed to revitalize the manufacturing and manufacturing-related services sector to engineer Malaysia’s reindustrialization second economic take-off. Specifically, NIMP 2030 strives to enhance the resilience of Malaysia’s, industries by. among others, fostering economic complexity, facilitating the adoption of technology, strengthening local industries' ecosystems, and elevating our industries’ position in the global supply chain., Transforming our manufacturing sector is critical towards achieving Malaysia's industrial, investment and export goals. While providing the necessary policy enablers is crucial to create a business- and investment-friendly industrial landscape, MITI is also focused on encouraging innovation, attracting strategic investments and facilitating trade.

Company Name: It is with great pleasure that the Federation of Malaysian Manufacturers (FMM) presents the 54th Edition of FMM Directory of Malaysian Industries. This comprehensive directory is a testament to our commitment to fostering strong business networks and promoting economic growth. Since 1969, this directory has evolved into a vital resource for both local and international traders, becoming one of the leading trade publications in the process.
Address: The manufacturing industry has undergone remarkable transformations, evolving from the mechanisation of the first industrial revolution to the automation and digitalisation of the third. Now, in the era of Industry 4.0, this evolutionary journey continues with the convergence of technologies, including artificial intelligence (Al), the Internet of Things (loT), big data analytics, and cloud computing. These advancements create a landscape where the physical and digital worlds seamlessly, While the manufacturing sector grapples with an array of challenges, from escalating costs and intensified global competition to the evolving preferences of customers, Industry 4.0 emerges as a transformative game-changer. It presents an opportunity for the sector to elevate productivity, product quality, and overall operational excellence. Through the adoption of Industry 4.0 principles, Malaysia can confront its current manufacturing challenges head-on, and strategically positions itself as a forward-thinking hub. In line with this, FMM is committed to continue promoting digital transformation and industry 4.0 initiatives to harness the full potential of the digital era to drive innovation and sustainable economic growth., In the current landscape of progress, it is essential to acknowledge the New Industrial Master Plan (NIMP 2030), recently launched in September 2023. Aligned with the MADANI Economy's vision and objectives, NIMP 2030 is poised to create a conducive ecosystem that supports the nation's transformation into a high-tech industrialised powerhouse. FMM firmly believes that NIMP 2030's mission-based approach, focusing on nurturing higher economic complexity and aggressively embracing technology, is vital in driving Malaysia to its next level of industrialisation and growth. This approach, underscored by sustainability and inclusivity principles, stands as a strategic pillar in our journey toward becoming a developed nation with high-income status., As we unveil the latest edition of FMM Directory of Malaysian Industries, we extend our sincere gratitude to all members, partners, and contributors who have made this publication possible. Your continued commitment is the cornerstone of our success and ensures the relevance of this directory. May this publication serve as a catalyst for growth, fostering collaboration and innovation within our dynamic industrial landscape.
